      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"4. MAHO BAY created a favourable impression making a winning debut at Kempton over 2220m and the son of Dubawi looks capable of following up after a break. Rates a leading contender. 1. AMADEUS MOZART also scored first time out when successful at the Curragh last spring. With natural progress commands major respect. 3. GUILDMASTER landed a success as a newcomer at Lingfield contesting 1600m four months ago and remains open to plenty of improvement. 5. GALIYAN is an interesting newcomer by Galiway out of Via Manzoni whose pedigree offers encouragement. Worth paying close attention in the market.\",\"runners\":[4,1,3,5],\"exclusive\":false}",
